ce.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Park%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nixon%20would%20spend%20the%20first%20nine%20years%20of%20his%20life%20here%20before%20moving%20to%20Whittier%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20ownership%20of%20the%20home%20changed%20over%20time%2C%20it%20was%20restored%20prior%20to%20the%20opening%20of%20Nixon's%20Library%20in%201990%20and%20is%20now%20a%20National%20Historic%20Landmark%20open%20to%20visitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Plains%2C%20Georgia%2C%20farm%20where%20Jimmy%20Carter%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20childhood%20had%20no%20indoor%20electricity%20or%20plumbing%20and%20relied%20on%20wood%20stoves%20for%20heat.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222684%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jimmy%20carter%20boyhood%20farm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f9c37e369331a0011bc657a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222012%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20farm%20where%20Jimmy%20Carter%20grew%20up.%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20M.%20Frank%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarter's%20family%20moved%20to%20this%20farm%20when%20he%20was%204%20years%20old.%20He%20helped%20his%20father%2C%20Earl%2C%20raise%20cotton%2C%20corn%2C%20peanuts%2C%20and%20sugar%20cane%2C%20all%20of%20which%20they%20sold%20alongside%20other%20items%20including%20coffee%20and%20kerosene%20at%20a%20country%20store%20near%20their%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fnr%2Ftravel%2Fpresidents%2Fjimmy_carter_nhs.html%5C%22%3ENational%20Park%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%20quotes%20Carter%20as%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20early%20years%20of%20my%20life%20on%20the%20farm%20were%20full%20and%20enjoyable%2C%20isolated%20but%20not%20lonely.%20We%20always%20had%20enough%20to%20eat%2C%20no%20economic%20hardship%2C%20but%20no%20money%20to%20waste.%20We%20felt%20close%20to%20nature%2C%20close%20to%20members%20of%20our%20family%2C%20and%20close%20to%20God.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20was%20born%20in%201942%20and%20spent%20the%20first%2010%20years%20of%20his%20life%20living%20with%20his%20maternal%20grandparents%20in%20Scranton%2C%20Pennsylvania.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223909%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Joe%20Biden%20childhood%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6023ec5ccca90200129b7693%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222932%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20childhood%20home.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Nickelsberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20not%20the%20most%20humble%20of%20houses%20on%20this%20list%2C%20it's%20still%20less%20glamorous%20than%20many%20other%20former%20presidents'%20childhood%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20lived%20in%20the%20three-story%20house%20at%202446%20N.%20Washington%20Ave.%20until%20the%20age%20of%2010%20with%20his%20maternal%20grandparents%2C%20the%20Finnegans%2C%20who%20owned%20the%20house%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2008%2F10%2F24%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2F24biden.html%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bidens%20left%20Scranton%20because%20of%20a%20weakening%20job%20market.%20After%20commuting%20to%20his%20job%20as%20a%20boiler%20cleaner%20for%20a%20heating%20and%20cooling%20company%20in%20Wilmington%2C%20Delaware%2C%20for%20some%20time%2C%20Joe%20Biden%20Sr.%20moved%20the%20family%20to%20an%20apartment%20in%20Claymont%2C%20Delaware%2C%20in%201953.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Bush%20family%20lived%20in%20this%201%2C400-square-foot%20home%20in%20Midland%2C%20Texas.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222633%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22george%20bush%20childhood%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f9c60766f5b3100117248bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221975%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Bush%20and%20first%20lady%20Laura%2